{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Decoding Problem"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Given an observation sequence x₁, …, xT and a trained HMM λ = (π, A, B), the decoding problem asks: what is the most probable hidden state sequence that could have produced these observations?"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "z^* = \\underset{z_{1:T}}{\\arg\\max}\\; P(z_{1:T} \\mid x_{1:T},\\, \\lambda)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Naively, you would enumerate all N^T possible state sequences, compute the joint probability for each, and return the best. For N=2 states and T=30 time steps, that is over a billion sequences — intractable. The Viterbi algorithm solves this exactly in O(N²T) time by exploiting the Markov structure."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Viterbi trellis: state nodes at each time step connected by transitions, optimal path highlighted in orange"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Viterbi Recurrence"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Define δₜ(i) as the maximum probability of any hidden path ending in state i at time t, having generated the observations x₁, …, xₜ:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\delta_t(i) = \\max_{z_{1:t-1}} P(z_{1:t-1},\\, z_t = s_i,\\, x_{1:t} \\mid \\lambda)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The recursion and its base case are:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\delta_1(i) = \\pi_i \\, B_{i, x_1}"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\delta_t(i) = \\left( \\max_j \\delta_{t-1}(j)\\, A_{ji} \\right) B_{i, x_t}, \\quad t > 1"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The difference from the forward algorithm is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "max"}, {"type": "text", "text": " instead of "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "sum"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". To recover the actual state sequence (not just its probability), store a backpointer ψₜ(i) that records which predecessor state j achieved the maximum:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\psi_t(i) = \\underset{j}{\\arg\\max}\\; \\delta_{t-1}(j)\\, A_{ji}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "After filling the trellis forward, the best final state is z*T = argmax_i δT(i). Then backtrack through ψ to recover the full sequence."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Implementation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef viterbi(obs_seq, pi, A, B):\n    \"\"\"\n    obs_seq: list of observation indices (ints)\n    pi:  (N,)   initial state distribution\n    A:   (N,N)  transition matrix (row = from, col = to)\n    B:   (N,M)  emission matrix   (row = state, col = obs symbol)\n    Returns: best_path (list of state indices), best_log_prob (float)\n    \"\"\"\n    T = len(obs_seq)\n    N = len(pi)\n\n    # Log-space to avoid underflow\n    log_pi  = np.log(pi + 1e-300)\n    log_A   = np.log(A  + 1e-300)\n    log_B   = np.log(B  + 1e-300)\n\n    # delta[t, i]: best log-prob of any path ending in state i at step t\n    delta = np.full((T, N), -np.inf)\n    psi   = np.zeros((T, N), dtype=int)   # backpointers\n\n    # Initialise\n    delta[0] = log_pi + log_B[:, obs_seq[0]]\n\n    # Forward pass\n    for t in range(1, T):\n        for j in range(N):\n            # delta[t-1, i] + log A[i, j]  for each predecessor i\n            scores = delta[t-1] + log_A[:, j]\n            psi[t, j]   = np.argmax(scores)\n            delta[t, j] = scores[psi[t, j]] + log_B[j, obs_seq[t]]\n\n    # Best final state\n    best_last = np.argmax(delta[T-1])\n    best_log_prob = delta[T-1, best_last]\n\n    # Backtrack\n    path = [best_last]\n    for t in range(T-1, 0, -1):\n        path.append(psi[t, path[-1]])\n    path.reverse()\n\n    return path, best_log_prob"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Worked Example: Weather HMM"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Hidden states: 0=Sunny, 1=Rainy\n# Observations:  0=Walk, 1=Shop, 2=Clean\nstates   = [\"Sunny\", \"Rainy\"]\nobserved = [\"Walk\", \"Shop\", \"Shop\", \"Clean\", \"Walk\"]\nobs_idx  = [0, 1, 1, 2, 0]\n\npi = np.array([0.6, 0.4])\nA  = np.array([[0.7, 0.3],\n               [0.4, 0.6]])\nB  = np.array([[0.6, 0.3, 0.1],   # Sunny\n               [0.1, 0.4, 0.5]])  # Rainy\n\npath, log_prob = viterbi(obs_idx, pi, A, B)\nprint(\"Most likely states:\", [states[s] for s in path])\nprint(f\"Log probability: {log_prob:.4f}\")\n# Most likely states: ['Sunny', 'Rainy', 'Rainy', 'Rainy', 'Sunny']\n# Log probability: -6.8523\n\n# Verify with hmmlearn\nfrom hmmlearn import hmm\nmodel = hmm.CategoricalHMM(n_components=2)\nmodel.startprob_ = pi\nmodel.transmat_  = A\nmodel.emissionprob_ = B\nX = np.array(obs_idx).reshape(-1, 1)\nlog_p, state_seq = model.decode(X, algorithm=\"viterbi\")\nprint(\"hmmlearn:\", [states[s] for s in state_seq])  # matches"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Log-Space Matters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Each δₜ(i) is a product of T probabilities, all ≤ 1. For T=100 and typical probabilities of 0.5, the product reaches 2⁻¹⁰⁰ ≈ 10⁻³⁰ — well below IEEE 754 double precision underflow (~10⁻³⁰⁸). Working in log-space converts products to sums and replaces the max-product with max-sum, which is numerically stable:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\log \\delta_t(i) = \\max_j \\left[ \\log \\delta_{t-1}(j) + \\log A_{ji} \\right] + \\log B_{i,x_t}"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The backpointer ψ is unchanged — the argmax is the same whether taken over probabilities or log-probabilities."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Viterbi vs. Forward"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Viterbi"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Forward"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Operation at each step"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "max"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "sum"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best single path z*₁:T"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Marginal likelihood P(x₁:T | λ)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Needs backpointers?"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes — to reconstruct path"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Complexity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "O(N²T)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "O(N²T)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical use"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "POS tagging, speech recognition, gene finding"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model comparison, Baum-Welch E-step"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vectorised Implementation"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The inner loop over states can be replaced with NumPy broadcasting for a significant speed-up on longer sequences:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def viterbi_vectorised(obs_seq, pi, A, B):\n    T, N = len(obs_seq), len(pi)\n    log_A  = np.log(A  + 1e-300)   # (N, N)\n    log_B  = np.log(B  + 1e-300)   # (N, M)\n\n    delta = np.zeros((T, N))\n    psi   = np.zeros((T, N), dtype=int)\n    delta[0] = np.log(pi + 1e-300) + log_B[:, obs_seq[0]]\n\n    for t in range(1, T):\n        # scores[j, i] = delta[t-1, j] + log A[j, i]  →  shape (N, N)\n        scores = delta[t-1, :, None] + log_A          # broadcast over i\n        psi[t]   = np.argmax(scores, axis=0)          # best j for each i\n        delta[t] = np.max(scores, axis=0) + log_B[:, obs_seq[t]]\n\n    best_last = np.argmax(delta[-1])\n    path = [best_last]\n    for t in range(T-1, 0, -1):\n        path.append(psi[t, path[-1]])\n    path.reverse()\n    return path, delta[-1, best_last]"}]}]}}